<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="7" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,310,1880,1906]" box="[189,310,1880,1906]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1880,1906]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1880,1906]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1398,1927,2025]" lastBlockId="6.[187,1399,265,484]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="7" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Recognized by the following characters: coloration distinctly black and white, with head, pronotum, clavus, transverse spot on medioapical part of corium, apex of cuneus, and cells uniformly dark brown to black, remaining part of hemelytron and legs contrastingly whitish (
<figureCitation box="[1117,1251,1998,2024]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="43.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[255,1348,414,1811]" captionTargetId="figure-12@43.[189,1398,376,1856]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="Fig. 2. Habitus of Ernestinus, Harpedona and Lopidolon spp. A. Ernestinus mimicus Distant, 1911, ♂, UASB. B. Ernestinus ramkeshariae Yasunaga &amp; Ishikawa, 2016, ♂, UASB. C. Harpedona sanguinipes Distant, 1904, ♂, UASB. D. Harpedona vittlaensis sp. nov, ♀, UASB. E–F. Lopidolon dandeliensis sp. nov., UASB. E. ♂. F. ♀." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690366" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690366/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Figs 2A–B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1265,1384,1998,2025]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="67.[189,232,1893,1919]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,336,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-61@67.[189,1398,336,1854]" captionTargetPageId="67" captionText="Fig. 26. Habitats and living specimens. A–C. Ernestinus ramkeshariae Yasunaga &amp; Ishikawa, 2016 on Colocasia esculenta. A. Nymphs. B–C. Adult. D–F. Ernestinus mimicus Distant, 1911 on Lagenandra sp. D. Aquatic habitat. E. Nymph and freshly moulted adult. F. Adult. All specimens at UASB." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690419" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690419/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">26B–C, F</figureCitation>
); antenna whitish with entirely or apically darkened segment II; pronotum densely and coarsely punctate, campaniform, distinctly raised posteriorly and covering entire mesoscutum and base of scutellum; calli located far from anterior margin of pronotum, delimited by shallow sulcus, medially separated by deep pit; genital capsule boat-shaped, without distinctive ornamentation (
<figureCitation box="[994,1108,380,406]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="53.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[204,1352,419,1782]" captionTargetId="figure-54@53.[189,1398,384,1893]" captionTargetPageId="53" captionText="Fig. 12. Male genitalia of Ernestinus mimicus Distant, 1911, UASB. A. Genital capsule in dorsal view. B–C. Right paramere in dorsal view and ventral views. D–E. Left paramere in dorsal and lateral views. F. Aedeagus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690388" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690388/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Figs 12A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1120,1175,380,406]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="54.[189,232,1927,1953]" captionTargetBox="[230,1375,386,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-74@54.[189,1398,367,1888]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="Fig. 13. Male genitalia of Ernestinus ramkeshariae Yasunaga &amp; Ishikawa, 2016, UASB. A. Genital capsule in dorsal view. B–D. Right paramere. B. Dorsal view. C. Ventral view. D. Apex, magnified. E–F. Left paramere. E. Dorsal view. F. Lateral view. G. Apex, magnified. H. Aedeagus in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690390" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690390/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">13A</figureCitation>
); aedeagus simple, tubular, usually C-shaped, with endosoma non-retractable, entirely expanded from phallotheca in repose, weakly sclerotized, and not clearly divided from phallotheca (
<figureCitation box="[913,1019,457,483]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="53.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[204,1352,419,1782]" captionTargetId="figure-54@53.[189,1398,384,1893]" captionTargetPageId="53" captionText="Fig. 12. Male genitalia of Ernestinus mimicus Distant, 1911, UASB. A. Genital capsule in dorsal view. B–C. Right paramere in dorsal view and ventral views. D–E. Left paramere in dorsal and lateral views. F. Aedeagus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690388" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690388/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Figs 12F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1030,1085,457,483]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="54.[189,232,1927,1953]" captionTargetBox="[230,1375,386,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-74@54.[189,1398,367,1888]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="Fig. 13. Male genitalia of Ernestinus ramkeshariae Yasunaga &amp; Ishikawa, 2016, UASB. A. Genital capsule in dorsal view. B–D. Right paramere. B. Dorsal view. C. Ventral view. D. Apex, magnified. E–F. Left paramere. E. Dorsal view. F. Lateral view. G. Apex, magnified. H. Aedeagus in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690390" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690390/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">13H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,248,526,552]" box="[189,248,526,552]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,248,526,552]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,248,526,552]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Host</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1399,575,679]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Adults and nymphs feed and aggregate on the abaxial surfaces of leaves of 
<taxonomicName box="[1121,1217,576,602]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Araceae</taxonomicName>
plants, mainly 
<taxonomicName box="[189,292,614,640]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Alocasia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[189,292,614,640]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Alocasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[312,508,614,640]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Amorphophallus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[312,508,614,640]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Amorphophallus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[585,704,614,640]" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Colocasia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[585,704,614,640]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Colocasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. 
<bibRefCitation author="Yasunaga Y. &amp; Ishikawa T." box="[778,1138,614,641]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="411 - 469" refId="ref23196" refString="Yasunaga Y. &amp; Ishikawa T. 2016. Twelve new species of the Asian plant bug genus Ernestinus Distant (Heteroptera: Miridae: Bryocorinae: Eccritotarsini), with emphasis on unique biology and descriptions of three additional new eccritotarsine species. Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution 47 (5): 411 - 469. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 1876312 X- 47052149" type="journal article" year="2016">
Yasunaga &amp; 
<collectingRegion box="[940,1046,614,640]" country="Japan" name="Ishikawa" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Ishikawa</collectingRegion>
(2016)
</bibRefCitation>
provided a uniquely detailed account of the natural history of the genus and each included species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[189,1399,721,797]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,342,721,747]" box="[189,342,721,747]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,342,721,747]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,342,721,747]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1399,771,797]" box="[189,1399,771,797]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Widely distributed in the Oriental Region and spanning north to 
<collectingCountry box="[938,1011,771,797]" name="Nepal" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Nepal</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1022,1108,771,797]" name="Taiwan" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
and southwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[1324,1395,771,797]" name="Japan" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Japan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,303,840,866]" box="[189,303,840,866]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,840,866]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,840,866]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[188,1399,889,1300]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Based on external morphology and the male genitalia, 
<bibRefCitation author="Stonedahl G. M." box="[856,1110,889,915]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 99" refId="ref23015" refString="Stonedahl G. M. 1988. Revisions of Dioclerus, Harpedona, Mertila, Myiocapsus, Prodromus and Thaumastomiris (Heteroptera: Miridae, Bryocorinae: Eccritotarsini). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 187: 1 - 99." type="journal article" year="1988">Stonedahl (1988: 43)</bibRefCitation>
outlined a group of six related genera including 
<taxonomicName authority=", Distant, 1911" authorityName=", Distant" authorityYear="1911" box="[489,789,927,954]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Ernestinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[489,612,928,953]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Ernestinus</emphasis>
, Distant, 1911
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Poppius, 1915" authorityName="Poppius" authorityYear="1915" box="[806,1089,927,954]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Eofurius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[806,907,928,954]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Eofurius</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Poppius B." box="[917,1089,927,954]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="75 - 88" refId="ref22888" refString="Poppius B. 1915. Neue orientalische Bryocorinen. Philippine Journal of Science 10: 75 - 88." type="journal article" year="1915">Poppius, 1915</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Poppius, 1914" authorityName="Poppius" authorityYear="1914" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Microbryocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1106,1289,927,953]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Microbryocoris</emphasis>
Poppius, 1914
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Poppius, 1914" authorityName="Poppius" authorityYear="1914" box="[268,598,966,992]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Myiocapsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[268,408,967,992]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Myiocapsus</emphasis>
Poppius, 1914
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Poppius, 1912" authorityName="Poppius" authorityYear="1912" box="[617,958,966,992]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Palaeofurius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[617,769,966,992]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Palaeofurius</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Poppius B." box="[782,958,966,992]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 27" refId="ref22862" refString="Poppius B. 1912. Zur Kenntnis der indo-australischen Bryocorinen. Ofversigt af Finska Vetenskapssocietetens Forhandlingar 54 A (30): 1 - 27." type="journal article" year="1912">Poppius, 1912</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Stonedahl, 1986" authorityName="Stonedahl" authorityYear="1986" box="[1033,1394,966,992]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Stylopomiris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1033,1181,966,992]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Stylopomiris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Stonedahl G. M." box="[1194,1394,966,992]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="226 - 234" refId="ref22972" refString="Stonedahl G. M. 1986. Stylopomiris, a new genus and three species of Eccritotarsini (Heteroptera: Miridae: Bryocorinae) from Viet Nam and Malaya. Journal of the New York Entomological Society 94: 226 - 234." type="journal article" year="1986">Stonedahl, 1986</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Of these, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Poppius" authorityYear="1914" box="[315,498,1004,1030]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Microbryocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[315,498,1004,1030]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Microbryocoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Poppius" authorityYear="1914" box="[519,659,1005,1030]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Myiocapsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[519,659,1005,1030]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Myiocapsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stonedahl" authorityYear="1986" box="[736,884,1004,1030]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Stylopomiris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[736,884,1004,1030]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Stylopomiris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
readily differ from 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Distant" authorityYear="1911" box="[1140,1265,1005,1030]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Ernestinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1140,1265,1005,1030]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Ernestinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in several autapomorphic traits (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Stonedahl G. M." box="[491,676,1043,1069]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="226 - 234" refId="ref22972" refString="Stonedahl G. M. 1986. Stylopomiris, a new genus and three species of Eccritotarsini (Heteroptera: Miridae: Bryocorinae) from Viet Nam and Malaya. Journal of the New York Entomological Society 94: 226 - 234." type="journal article" year="1986">Stonedahl 1986</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Stonedahl G. M." box="[687,746,1043,1069]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 99" refId="ref23015" refString="Stonedahl G. M. 1988. Revisions of Dioclerus, Harpedona, Mertila, Myiocapsus, Prodromus and Thaumastomiris (Heteroptera: Miridae, Bryocorinae: Eccritotarsini). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 187: 1 - 99." type="journal article" year="1988">1988</bibRefCitation>
for details). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Poppius" authorityYear="1915" box="[893,994,1043,1069]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Eofurius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[893,994,1043,1069]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Eofurius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a monotypic genus known from a single male collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[475,607,1081,1107]" name="Philippines" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Philippines</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Poppius B." box="[622,788,1081,1108]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="75 - 88" refId="ref22888" refString="Poppius B. 1915. Neue orientalische Bryocorinen. Philippine Journal of Science 10: 75 - 88." type="journal article" year="1915">Poppius 1915</bibRefCitation>
), has not been studied since the original description but differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Distant" authorityYear="1911" box="[393,518,1120,1145]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Ernestinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[393,518,1120,1145]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Ernestinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. in the small size and substantially produced clypeus. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Poppius" authorityYear="1912" box="[1247,1399,1120,1146]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Palaeofurius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1247,1399,1120,1146]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Palaeofurius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
contains three species from 
<collectingCountry box="[514,739,1158,1185]" name="Papua New Guinea" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Papua New Guinea</collectingCountry>
and appears to be most closely related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Distant" authorityYear="1911" box="[1223,1348,1159,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Ernestinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1223,1348,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Ernestinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to the same pattern of coloration, structure of pronotum, parameres, and characteristic aedeagus (see Carvalho 1981). 
<bibRefCitation author="Yasunaga Y. &amp; Ishikawa T." box="[386,727,1235,1262]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="411 - 469" refId="ref23196" refString="Yasunaga Y. &amp; Ishikawa T. 2016. Twelve new species of the Asian plant bug genus Ernestinus Distant (Heteroptera: Miridae: Bryocorinae: Eccritotarsini), with emphasis on unique biology and descriptions of three additional new eccritotarsine species. Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution 47 (5): 411 - 469. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 1876312 X- 47052149" type="journal article" year="2016">Yasunaga &amp; Ishikawa (2016)</bibRefCitation>
correctly pointed out that this taxon might be a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Distant" authorityYear="1911" box="[221,346,1274,1299]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Ernestinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[221,346,1274,1299]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Ernestinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but refrained from formal action due to the lack of material.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1399,1342,1676]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Distant" authorityYear="1911" box="[327,452,1343,1368]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Ernestinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[327,452,1343,1368]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Ernestinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
share a number of common features in the structure of head, pronotum and especially male genitalia with those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Carvalho, 1981" authorityName="Carvalho" authorityYear="1981" box="[654,1003,1380,1407]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Ambunticoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[654,812,1380,1406]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Ambunticoris</emphasis>
Carvalho, 1981
</taxonomicName>
, a genus containing three species from New 
<collectingCountry box="[323,408,1419,1445]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Guinea</collectingCountry>
and Sulawesi (Konstantinov &amp; Zinovjeva 2006). However, it clearly differs from that genus and other Oriental eccritotarsines in the color pattern and many additional traits documented by 
<bibRefCitation author="Yasunaga Y. &amp; Ishikawa T." box="[225,572,1496,1523]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="411 - 469" refId="ref23196" refString="Yasunaga Y. &amp; Ishikawa T. 2016. Twelve new species of the Asian plant bug genus Ernestinus Distant (Heteroptera: Miridae: Bryocorinae: Eccritotarsini), with emphasis on unique biology and descriptions of three additional new eccritotarsine species. Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution 47 (5): 411 - 469. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 1876312 X- 47052149" type="journal article" year="2016">Yasunaga &amp; Ishikawa (2016)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Lin, 2001" authorityName="Lin" authorityYear="2001" box="[584,910,1496,1522]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Ernestinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevis">
<emphasis box="[584,788,1496,1522]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Ernestinus brevis</emphasis>
Lin, 2001
</taxonomicName>
described from 
<collectingCountry box="[1102,1188,1496,1522]" name="Taiwan" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lin C. - S." box="[1204,1327,1496,1522]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="29 - 35" refId="ref22309" refString="Lin C. - S. 2001 a. Genus Ernestinus Distant (Hemiptera: Miridae) of Taiwan. Formosan Entomologist 21: 29 - 35." type="journal article" year="2001">Lin 2001a</bibRefCitation>
) is an exception in having pale greenish pronotum, scutellum and hemelytron; its generic placement requires further verification (
<bibRefCitation author="Yasunaga Y. &amp; Ishikawa T." box="[422,746,1572,1599]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="411 - 469" refId="ref23196" refString="Yasunaga Y. &amp; Ishikawa T. 2016. Twelve new species of the Asian plant bug genus Ernestinus Distant (Heteroptera: Miridae: Bryocorinae: Eccritotarsini), with emphasis on unique biology and descriptions of three additional new eccritotarsine species. Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution 47 (5): 411 - 469. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 1876312 X- 47052149" type="journal article" year="2016">Yasunaga &amp; Ishikawa 2016</bibRefCitation>
). The genus was originally described from 
<collectingCountry box="[1238,1351,1572,1598]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
and currently includes 19 Southeast Asian species (
<bibRefCitation author="Yasunaga Y. &amp; Ishikawa T." box="[747,1081,1611,1638]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="411 - 469" refId="ref23196" refString="Yasunaga Y. &amp; Ishikawa T. 2016. Twelve new species of the Asian plant bug genus Ernestinus Distant (Heteroptera: Miridae: Bryocorinae: Eccritotarsini), with emphasis on unique biology and descriptions of three additional new eccritotarsine species. Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution 47 (5): 411 - 469. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 1876312 X- 47052149" type="journal article" year="2016">Yasunaga &amp; Ishikawa 2016</bibRefCitation>
). Examination of available material allowed us to note this genus from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Poppius" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[705,765,1649,1675]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="India" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">India</taxonomicName>
for the first time.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,956,1718,1744]" box="[189,956,1718,1744]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,956,1718,1744]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,956,1718,1744]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Key to species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Distant" authorityYear="1911" box="[530,662,1718,1744]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Ernestinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[530,662,1718,1744]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Ernestinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Poppius" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[701,768,1718,1744]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="India" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">India</taxonomicName>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[830,956,1718,1744]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<key pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1400,1768,2025]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
1. Antennal segment I dark brown with a dirty yellow base, segment II at least 1.3× as long as head width. Scutellum black (
<figureCitation box="[533,624,1806,1832]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="43.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[255,1348,414,1811]" captionTargetId="figure-12@43.[189,1398,376,1856]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="Fig. 2. Habitus of Ernestinus, Harpedona and Lopidolon spp. A. Ernestinus mimicus Distant, 1911, ♂, UASB. B. Ernestinus ramkeshariae Yasunaga &amp; Ishikawa, 2016, ♂, UASB. C. Harpedona sanguinipes Distant, 1904, ♂, UASB. D. Harpedona vittlaensis sp. nov, ♀, UASB. E–F. Lopidolon dandeliensis sp. nov., UASB. E. ♂. F. ♀." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690366" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690366/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig 2A</figureCitation>
). Left paramere strongly swollen at middle, with apical process long, almost straight, abruptly bent at base. Right paramere flag-shaped, wide (
<figureCitation box="[1160,1244,1845,1871]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="53.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[204,1352,419,1782]" captionTargetId="figure-54@53.[189,1398,384,1893]" captionTargetPageId="53" captionText="Fig. 12. Male genitalia of Ernestinus mimicus Distant, 1911, UASB. A. Genital capsule in dorsal view. B–C. Right paramere in dorsal view and ventral views. D–E. Left paramere in dorsal and lateral views. F. Aedeagus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690388" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690388/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) ................. .................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Distant, 1911" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1911" box="[1097,1399,1883,1909]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Ernestinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mimicus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1097,1234,1883,1909]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">E. mimicus</emphasis>
Distant, 1911
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1400,1768,2025]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis box="[193,208,1922,1947]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">–</emphasis>
Antennal segment I whitish yellow, segment II short, subequal to head width. Scutellum reddish orange medially (
<figureCitation box="[447,543,1960,1986]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="43.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[255,1348,414,1811]" captionTargetId="figure-12@43.[189,1398,376,1856]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="Fig. 2. Habitus of Ernestinus, Harpedona and Lopidolon spp. A. Ernestinus mimicus Distant, 1911, ♂, UASB. B. Ernestinus ramkeshariae Yasunaga &amp; Ishikawa, 2016, ♂, UASB. C. Harpedona sanguinipes Distant, 1904, ♂, UASB. D. Harpedona vittlaensis sp. nov, ♀, UASB. E–F. Lopidolon dandeliensis sp. nov., UASB. E. ♂. F. ♀." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690366" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690366/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Left paramere thinner, gradually curved along entire length, apically tapering. Right paramere bulbous (
<figureCitation box="[643,728,1998,2024]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="54.[189,232,1927,1953]" captionTargetBox="[230,1375,386,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-74@54.[189,1398,367,1888]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="Fig. 13. Male genitalia of Ernestinus ramkeshariae Yasunaga &amp; Ishikawa, 2016, UASB. A. Genital capsule in dorsal view. B–D. Right paramere. B. Dorsal view. C. Ventral view. D. Apex, magnified. E–F. Left paramere. E. Dorsal view. F. Lateral view. G. Apex, magnified. H. Aedeagus in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690390" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690390/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
) ............... 
<taxonomicName authority="Yasunaga &amp; Ishikawa, 2016" authorityName="Yasunaga &amp; Ishikawa" authorityYear="2016" box="[861,1399,1998,2025]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Ernestinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ramkeshariae">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[861,1061,1998,2025]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">E. ramkeshariae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Yasunaga Y. &amp; Ishikawa T." box="[1069,1399,1998,2025]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="411 - 469" refId="ref23196" refString="Yasunaga Y. &amp; Ishikawa T. 2016. Twelve new species of the Asian plant bug genus Ernestinus Distant (Heteroptera: Miridae: Bryocorinae: Eccritotarsini), with emphasis on unique biology and descriptions of three additional new eccritotarsine species. Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution 47 (5): 411 - 469. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 1876312 X- 47052149" type="journal article" year="2016">Yasunaga &amp; Ishikawa, 2016</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
